text: If you’ve been following me on social media lately you’ve probably already put two and two together. I’m really excited to announce that I’ll be returning to triathlon, a sport I’ve always been passionate about, for 2019 and hopefully beyond. Cycling has given me a lot and I’ll always be thankful for my time in the peloton, racing with some of the greatest athletes and mates I’ve ever met, but I’m excited to chase personal success in the sport of triathlon. Most of you may not know this but I have a history of competing in the sport and in 2009 I won the World Age group Championships as a 16 year old. I will be focusing on the Ironman 70.3 distance initially as I work on my swimming and running. I’m very fortunate to have the support of a few key partners early on in this journey, one of which is Ventum, the other is Incrediwear. I’ll be posting more about Ventum, Incrediwear and my other partners in the coming weeks, as well as sharing my journey, with all its ups, downs, challenges and triumphs here. I hope you’ll continue to follow me through this “transition”. || 📷 @kitkarzen || #triathlon #thetransition
